---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import DaylightHoursCalculator from '../components/DaylightHoursCalculator.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="Daylight Hours Calculator — Hours of Sunlight by Location & Date | Clockr"
	description="Find how many hours of daylight any city gets on any date. Compare with solstices, see sunrise and sunset times, and view a 24-hour daylight chart."
	category="seasons"
>
	<div class="sc-page">
		<div class="sc-header">
			<div class="sc-eyebrow">
				<span class="sc-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				SEASONS
			</div>
			<h1 class="sc-title">
				<span class="sc-gradient">Daylight Hours Calculator</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="sc-subtitle">
				Find out how many hours of daylight any location gets on any date
			</p>
		</div>

		<DaylightHoursCalculator client:load />

		<!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
		<section class="sc-how">
			<h2 class="sc-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="sc-how-card">
				<p>
					Daylight hours are not the same everywhere, or on every day of the year.
					Earth is tilted about 23.5° on its axis as it orbits the Sun, so
					different hemispheres lean toward or away from the Sun at different
					times. That tilt is why summer days are longer and winter nights are
					longer — and why the change is gradual through spring and autumn. This
					calculator uses the same solar-position algorithm as our Sun Calculator
					(based on NOAA/USNO methods) with each city&apos;s latitude and
					longitude to work out exactly how many minutes of daylight fall between
					sunrise and sunset on your chosen date.
				</p>
				<p>
					Latitude has a dramatic effect on daylight length. Near the equator —
					in cities like Singapore or Nairobi — day length stays close to 12
					hours all year. Move toward the poles and the seasonal swing grows:
					London gains roughly eight hours of daylight between the winter and
					summer solstices, while Reykjavik can have nearly 21 hours of light in
					June and under five in December. Your latitude sets the range of
					possible daylight; the date tells you where you are within that range.
				</p>
				<p>
					At extreme latitudes, daylight can behave in remarkable ways. Above the
					Arctic Circle in summer, the Sun may not set at all — a phenomenon
					called the <strong>midnight sun</strong>. In winter, the opposite occurs:
					<strong>polar night</strong>, when the Sun stays below the horizon for
					weeks. This calculator shows these edge cases clearly and lets you
					compare any date with the summer and winter solstices, or the same
					date last year, to see how daylight is changing where you live.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- FAQ -->
		<section class="sc-faq">
			<h2 class="sc-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="sc-faq-list">
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question"
						>How many hours of daylight are there today?</summary
					>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Select your city and leave the date on today (or tap the
							&ldquo;Today&rdquo; quick link). The total daylight hours and
							minutes appear at the top of the results, along with sunrise and
							sunset times in local time for that city. Daylight length changes
							slightly every day as Earth moves along its orbit.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question"
						>Which day has the most daylight hours?</summary
					>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							In the Northern Hemisphere, the summer solstice (around 21 June)
							has the longest day; in the Southern Hemisphere, that date is the
							winter solstice with the shortest day. Tap &ldquo;Summer
							Solstice&rdquo; to see the maximum daylight for your location in
							the current year. High-latitude cities see the biggest totals —
							sometimes over 20 hours.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question"
						>Which day has the fewest daylight hours?</summary
					>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							The winter solstice (around 21 December in the Northern Hemisphere)
							has the shortest day and fewest daylight hours. Use the
							&ldquo;Winter Solstice&rdquo; quick link or check the comparison
							table below the main result. Cities far from the equator can have
							very short December days — under six hours in some places.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question"
						>Why do daylight hours change throughout the year?</summary
					>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Earth&apos;s 23.5° axial tilt means the Northern and Southern
							Hemispheres take turns leaning toward the Sun as we orbit. When
							your hemisphere tilts toward the Sun, days grow longer; when it
							tilts away, nights grow longer. The change is fastest around the
							equinoxes (when day and night are nearly equal) and slowest near
							the solstices.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question"
						>Does latitude affect how many daylight hours you get?</summary
					>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Yes — latitude is one of the biggest factors. The equator gets
							roughly 12 hours of daylight year-round. As you move toward the
							poles, seasonal variation increases. Compare two cities at
							different latitudes using the location search to see the
							difference, especially on the solstice quick links.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question"
						>What is the longest day of the year?</summary
					>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							The longest day is the summer solstice — astronomically the moment
							when the Sun reaches its highest point in the sky for the year, which
							usually falls on 20, 21, or 22 June in the Northern Hemisphere
							(and around 21 December in the Southern Hemisphere). It is not
							always the earliest sunrise or latest sunset; those can differ by a
							few days due to Earth&apos;s elliptical orbit and time-zone rules.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- RELATED TOOLS -->
		<div class="sc-related">
			<h3 class="sc-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="sc-related-grid">
				<a href="/sun-calculator" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Sun Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/season-countdown" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Season Countdown</span></a
				>
				<a href="/clock-change-countdown" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Clock Change Countdown</span></a
				>
				<a href="/moon-phase-calculator" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Moon Phase Calculator</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
	.sc-page {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px;
	}

	.sc-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.sc-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-eyebrow-square {
		width: 8px;
		height: 8px;
		border-radius: 2px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		flex-shrink: 0;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: initial;
	}

	.sc-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-gradient {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sc-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.sc-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.sc-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.sc-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.sc-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.sc-how-card strong {
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.sc-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.sc-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.sc-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.sc-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sc-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.sc-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sc-faq-item[open] .sc-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.sc-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.sc-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.sc-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.sc-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.sc-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.sc-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.4);
	}

	.sc-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.sc-title {
			font-size: 44px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		.sc-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}

	/* Daylight Hours Calculator tool */
	.dhc-tool {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.dhc-inputs {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 20px;
		margin-bottom: 20px;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.dhc-inputs {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}

	.dhc-label {
		display: block;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
		margin-bottom: 8px;
	}

	.dhc-location-wrap {
		position: relative;
	}

	.dhc-location-input {
		width: 100%;
		box-sizing: border-box;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.25);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 14px 16px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: #fff;
		outline: none;
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			box-shadow 0.2s ease;
	}

	.dhc-location-input:focus {
		border-color: rgba(116, 180, 155, 0.6);
		box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
	}

	.dhc-location-input::placeholder {
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
		font-weight: 500;
	}

	.dhc-picker-list {
		position: absolute;
		top: calc(100% + 6px);
		left: 0;
		right: 0;
		z-index: 20;
		max-height: 280px;
		overflow-y: auto;
		margin: 0;
		padding: 6px;
		list-style: none;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.3);
		border-radius: 12px;
		box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
	}

	.dhc-picker-item {
		display: block;
		width: 100%;
		padding: 10px 12px;
		background: none;
		border: none;
		border-radius: 8px;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.75);
		text-align: left;
		cursor: pointer;
		transition: background 0.15s ease;
	}

	.dhc-picker-item:hover {
		background: rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
	}

	.dhc-picker-empty {
		padding: 12px;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
		text-align: center;
	}

	.dhc-date-wrap {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: flex-start;
	}

	.dhc-quick-dates {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 8px;
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	.dhc-quick-btn {
		padding: 8px 14px;
		background: rgba(12, 12, 12, 0.6);
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.25);
		border-radius: 999px;
		cursor: pointer;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			background 0.2s ease;
	}

	.dhc-quick-btn:hover {
		border-color: rgba(116, 180, 155, 0.5);
		background: rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.08);
	}

	.dhc-quick-btn--active {
		border-color: rgba(116, 180, 155, 0.7);
		background: rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
		color: #fff;
	}

	.dhc-hero-band {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		width: 100vw;
		margin-left: calc(50% - 50vw);
		padding: 48px 24px 56px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0d1f17, #1a2e24);
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.25);
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.25);
		margin-bottom: 40px;
	}

	.dhc-hero-centre {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		text-align: center;
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 640px;
	}

	.dhc-result-location {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65);
		margin: 0 0 6px;
	}

	.dhc-result-date {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		margin: 0 0 24px;
	}

	.dhc-daylight-hero {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(32px, 6vw, 48px);
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -1px;
		line-height: 1.1;
		margin: 0 0 20px;
		color: #fff;
	}

	.dhc-sun-times {
		display: flex;
		gap: 32px;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.dhc-sun-time {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 4px;
	}

	.dhc-sun-time-label {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 11px;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 1px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
	}

	.dhc-sun-time-value {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 800;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.dhc-chart-wrap {
		width: 100%;
	}

	.dhc-chart-bar {
		position: relative;
		height: 20px;
		background: #0a0a14;
		border-radius: 999px;
		overflow: visible;
		margin-bottom: 28px;
	}

	.dhc-chart-bar--polar {
		margin-bottom: 12px;
	}

	.dhc-chart-seg {
		position: absolute;
		top: 0;
		height: 100%;
		border-radius: 0;
	}

	.dhc-chart-seg--night {
		background: #0f172a;
	}

	.dhc-chart-seg--day {
		background: linear-gradient(90deg, #fbbf24, #f59e0b);
		box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.35);
	}

	.dhc-chart-tick {
		position: absolute;
		top: 100%;
		width: 2px;
		height: 10px;
		margin-left: -1px;
		margin-top: 2px;
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		z-index: 2;
	}

	.dhc-chart-tick-label {
		position: absolute;
		top: 14px;
		left: 50%;
		transform: translateX(-50%);
		white-space: nowrap;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 11px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
	}

	.dhc-chart-axis {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 11px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.35);
		margin-top: 4px;
	}

	.dhc-polar-note {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0 0 8px;
	}

	.dhc-compare {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.dhc-compare-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.dhc-compare-table-wrap {
		overflow-x: auto;
		border-radius: 14px;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
	}

	.dhc-compare-table {
		width: 100%;
		border-collapse: collapse;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
	}

	.dhc-compare-table th {
		text-align: left;
		padding: 14px 16px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
	}

	.dhc-compare-table td {
		padding: 14px 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65);
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
	}

	.dhc-compare-table tr:last-child td {
		border-bottom: none;
	}

	.dhc-compare-row--highlight td {
		color: #fff;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.08);
	}

	.dhc-compare-row--highlight td:nth-child(2) {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}
</style>
